Healthcare Equipment and Supplies

Company Overview of SynGen Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
SynGen Inc. develops, designs, and manufactures cell separation tools and accessories that focus on the recovery of target cells and depletion of contaminating cells. The company offers various medical devices, including SynGenX-1000 System, a closed sterile processing system that isolates and harvests stem and progenitor cells from umbilical cord blood; SynGen X-2000 System, a closed sterile processing system that is used in clinical laboratories, operating rooms, and physician office labs for the safe and rapid preparation of platelet-rich-plasma from a small sample of peripheral blood or a mixture of peripheral blood and bone marrow; and CryoPRO-2 cryopreservation/storage bag set, a singl...
SynGen Inc. develops, designs, and manufactures cell separation tools and accessories that focus on the recovery of target cells and depletion of contaminating cells. The company offers various medical devices, including SynGenX-1000 System, a closed sterile processing system that isolates and harvests stem and progenitor cells from umbilical cord blood; SynGen X-2000 System, a closed sterile processing system that is used in clinical laboratories, operating rooms, and physician office labs for the safe and rapid preparation of platelet-rich-plasma from a small sample of peripheral blood or a mixture of peripheral blood and bone marrow; and CryoPRO-2 cryopreservation/storage bag set, a single-closed system that eliminates the need for heat sealing the fluid bridges between large and small compartments. It also offers laboratory devices, including sterile docking workstations; SynGenX-Lab System, a solution for the extraction of target cell populations from bone marrow, peripheral blood, or cord blood samples for use in cell processing laboratories; and CryoPRO Workstation, a solution for adding cryoprotectant to cord blood buffy coat and transferring to freezing bag. In addition, the company offers SynGen DataTrak software, a clinical software system that downloads vital processing data from the control module and the CryoPRO Workstation to the operator’s laptop computer for inclusion in medical or manufacturing records; and SynGenCellWashPRO, a semi-automated laboratory device for washing expanded cell populations. It offers its products in Europe and internationally. The company was founded in 2007 and is based in Sacramento, California with an additional location in Runcorn, United Kingdom. As of July 7, 2017, SynGen Inc. operates as a subsidiary of ThermoGenesis Corp.
Detailed Description


