X-LAB | Syngen Inc.













































































































SynGenX®-LAB SystemA revolutionary new process to isolate cell populations from bone marrow, blood or apheresis products.





SynGenX®-LAB System


The SynGenX®-LAB System is designed for the efficient isolation of target cell populations from bone marrow, blood or apheresis products in a closed device. It is intended for use in cell processing laboratories. The SynGenX®-LAB System automatically harvests the target cell population from starting materials during a short cycle on a programmable bench top centrifuge without the use of Ficoll or other additives.
In addition, the system’s firmware and SynGen®-DataTrak software generate a report of the entire centrifugation and harvest process, downloadable to the host PC for cGMP compliance. The SynGenX®-LAB system is available in the US, EU and UK.



ORDER SynGenX®-LAB>
FeaturesHow it WorksSupport & ResourcesFeaturesSynGenX®-LAB FeaturesBetter integration for GMP support.


The SynGen® DataTrak software is installed on the host’s PC and is the user interface for the SynGenX®-Lab System. The software allows the operator of the system to use a bar code reader to track and record equipment serial numbers and disposable lot numbers. The software also downloads process performance data from the Control Module to the host PC that includes important cGMLP support information:

Tracking centrifuge performance, including duration of periods at constant speed, accelerations and decelerations.
Opening and closing of the valves that direct target cells and red blood cells to their respective compartments at the base of the Disposable Cartridge.
Configured volumes of harvested target cells.
Documentation of the successful completion of the processing cycle.
 Space for sign-off of the data set by the lab director, if desired.

 
 
*The SynGenX®-LAB system is designed for the efficient isolation of cell populations from bone marrow, blood or apheresis samples, and is classified as general laboratory equipment. 



ONE SYSTEM
Unprecedented ResultsKEY FEATURES




Highly efficient depletions and recoveries of target cell populations automatically, without the use of Ficoll.
15 to 30 minute processing time
Functionally closed system
Easy to Use



SYSTEM COMPONENTS




SynGenX®-LAB Disposable Cartridge
SynGenX®-LAB Control Module
SynGenX Docking Station
SynGen® DataTrak Software



How it WorksHow It Works





One unit, endless possibilities.



The SynGenX®-LAB System is designed for the efficient extraction of target cell populations from bone marrow or blood samples in a closed device.
The sample is transferred to the central sample chamber of the SynGenX®-LAB Disposable Cartridge via transfer tubing through a 150 micron filter to remove any clots and bone chips.








STEP #1Centrifugation







The Disposable Cartridge is latched onto the SynGenX®-LAB Control Module, placed in the centrifuge and counter balanced with a SynGen counterweight cartridge. During centrifugation, the sample is separated into three fractions:  red blood cells, target cells, and plasma.



STEP #2Stratification & Separation







The SynGenX®-LAB Disposable Cartridge features a cone-shaped region at the bottom of the central sample chamber where the cell fractions of the sample stratify during centrifugation.
Four vertically aligned, infrared sensor-pairs in the Control Module continuously monitor the region, detect cell fraction interfaces, and trigger opening and closing of the valves that direct the red blood cells and the target cells to their respective chambers.  This allows high precision separation and harvest of the target cells during processing.



STEP #3Analysis







The SynGenX®-LAB Docking Station transfers the data collected during the centrifuge run by the Control Module via SynGen™ DataTrak software installed on a PC.


Support & ResourcesSupport & ResourcesVisit SynGen's Support Center to access the Support Portal, FAQ's and more.





Enhanced Cell TherapySynGen's innovative, scalable systems increase target cell recovery and redefine the regenerative medicine workflow.System Components





SynGenX®-LAB Disposable Cartridge



Each SynGenX®-LAB Disposable Cartridge can process a sample of bone marrow, blood or apheresis product with a volume between 40 mL to 240 mL. The Disposable Cartridge has three discrete compartments for separation of the sample into a defined volume of target cells, depleted red blood cells and the remaining plasma.
The target cells can be collected from the harvest chamber via the attached access tube, either by sterile-welding a transfer bag or by syringe via a luer-lock fitting.  Four disposable cartridges can be processed simultaneously, enabling nearly 1 liter of starting material to be processed.








SynGenX®-LAB Control Module





Separation made easy.



The SynGenX®-LAB Control Module automatically directs the separation of the target cells, red cells and plasma into their respective chambers, by monitoring the  speed of the centrifuge, and opening and closing valves at the base of the Disposable Cartridge at the right times.








SynGenX Docking Station





Powerful. Efficient. Simple.



The SynGenX Docking Station transfers the data collected during the centrifuge run by the Control Module to the host PC via SynGen® DataTrak software. It also charges the Control Module’s lithium polymer ion battery. A fully charged battery will allow the Control Module to operate an average of 5 days of normal laboratory operation.


